DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGgraphmacros.pl",
  "MathObjects.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");
Context()->strings->add( none=>{} );

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a=random(3,9,2);
$b=random(3,19,2);

if ($a == $b) {$b = 2 * $a - 1};

$c=random(4,18,2);

$m= "$a/$b";
$k = "$c/$b";

BEGIN_TEXT

If possible write the following equation in $BBOLD slope-intercept $EBOLD form.
\[ $a x - $b y + $c = 0 \]

$PAR
a) What is the value of \(m\) when written in slope-intercept form?  If the equation cannot be written in slope-intercept form, enter ${BBOLD}none$EBOLD in the box.
$BR
\( m = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
$PAR
b) What is the value of \(b\) when written in slope-intercept form?  If the equation cannot be written in slope-intercept form, enter ${BBOLD}none$EBOLD in the box.$BR
\( b = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}

END_TEXT

ANS( Compute($m)->cmp() );
ANS( Compute($k)->cmp() );

($n,$d) = reduce( $a, $b );
$md = ( $d == 1 ) ? $n : "\frac{$n}{$d}";
($n,$d) = reduce( $c, $b );
$kd = ( $d == 1 ) ? $n : "\frac{$n}{$d}";

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR
Rewriting in slope-intercept form:
\[ $a x - $b y + $c = 0 \]
gives
\[ - $b y = - $a x - $c\]
so that
\[ y = $md x + $kd \]

END_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
